Exercise 1:
-----------
	Create Android test project. In this exercise we will create new Android
	Test Project and locate it under com.vogella.android.countries/test folder.

Steps:
	1. Open menu File - New - Other … - Android / Android Test Project
	2. * Project Name: “com.vogella.android.countries-test”
	     Uncheck “Use default location”
         Choose location “<workspace>/com.vogella.android.countries/tests”
         Press Next
       * An existing Android project: “com.vogella.android.countries”
	     Press Next
	   * Choose “Android 4.2.2”
	     Press Finish
	     
	Note: Eclipse creates “com.vogella.android.countries-test-test” folder 
	      under “com.vogella.android.countries” project. This is a bug in 
	      Eclipse. To fix this we will rename this folder to “tests” as 
	      following.
	
	3. Right mouse click on “com.vogella.android.countries-test-test” folder 
	   - Refactor - Rename - Enter new name “tests” - press OK.
	
	Note: Project “com.vogella.android.countries-test” will disappear from the
	      Eclipse workspace. Now we need to import our test project again as
	      following.
	      
	4. File - Import - Existing Project into Workspace - Select root directory 
	   / Browse - choose “<workspace>/com.vogella.android.countries/tests” 
	   location - press Finish.
	   
	   New project “com.vogella.android.countries-test” will appear in your
	   workspace. We are done.